{"questionId":"20276","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and its graph&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, showing clearly the value of the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept and the&nbsp;approximate position of point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"padding-left:90px;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3fe45d26d2e1fccb3d8104652d7c5c5e9bc22c34.png\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for one <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercept only, located at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em> for local maximum, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>P</mtext></math>, in approximately correct position<br><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A1</strong></em> for curve approaching <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math> (including change in concavity).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20276","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.8e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Sketch the graph of f, showing clearly the value of the x-intercept and the approximate position of point P.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.3—Graphing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}